<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
The only two specimens observed in Macau exhibited a total length of 9-9.5 mm and a maximum width of 4 mm. Its general morphology matches rather well that of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pterolophia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pterolophia cervina" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cervina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Pterolophia cervina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gressit, 1939 from Guangdong, which was recently considered as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Pascoe, 1865" authorityName="Pascoe" authorityYear="1866" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Praonetha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Praonetha consularis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="consularis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Praonetha consularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Pascoe, 1866 (
<bibRefCitation author="Weigel, A" journalOrPublisher="Formosa Ecological Company, Taiwan" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B155" refString="Weigel, A, Meng, L-Z, Lin, M-Y, 2013. Contribution to the Fauna of Longhorn Beetles in the Naban River Watershed National Nature Reserve. Formosa Ecological Company, Taiwan" title="Contribution to the Fauna of Longhorn Beetles in the Naban River Watershed National Nature Reserve." year="2013">Weigel et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
). It also resembles closely 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. (Mimoron) brevegibbosa" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="brevegibbosa" subGenus="Mimoron">P. (Mimoron) brevegibbosa</taxonomicName>
Pic, 1926 from Lantau Island, Hong Kong (
<bibRefCitation author="Hayashi, M" journalOrPublisher="The Entomological Review of Japan" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="71 - 74" publicationUrl="http://coleoptera.sakura.ne.jp/ERJ/ERJ37(1)1982.pdf" refId="B61" refString="Hayashi, M, 1982. On Some Cerambycidae from Hong Kong (Coleoptera). The Entomological Review of Japan 37 (1): 71 - 74, http://coleoptera.sakura.ne.jp/ERJ/ERJ37(1)1982.pdf" title="On Some Cerambycidae from Hong Kong (Coleoptera)." url="http://coleoptera.sakura.ne.jp/ERJ/ERJ37(1)1982.pdf" volume="37" year="1982">Hayashi 1982</bibRefCitation>
, pl. 2, fig. 6). So, it is possible that all of them actually represent the same species, with the name 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. (P.) consularis" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="consularis" subGenus="P.">P. (P.) consularis</taxonomicName>
being the most senior. However, if the type species from Malaysia is different, then 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. (M.) brevegibbosa" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="brevegibbosa" subGenus="M.">P. (M.) brevegibbosa</taxonomicName>
will be the senior name for the species from Macau, Guangdong, Hong Kong and Hainan Island. 
<bibRefCitation author="Yiu, V" journalOrPublisher="Hong Kong Entomological Society, Hong Kong" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B161" refString="Yiu, V, 2009. Longhorn Beetles of Hong Kong. Insect Fauna of Hong Kong, Fascicle 1. Hong Kong Entomological Society, Hong Kong" title="Longhorn Beetles of Hong Kong. Insect Fauna of Hong Kong, Fascicle 1." year="2009">Yiu (2009)</bibRefCitation>
reported that larvae of this species in Hong Kong bore into plants of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Zea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Zea mays" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="mays">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Zea mays</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Hua, L-Z" journalOrPublisher="List of Chinese Insects" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="1 - 612" refId="B68" refString="Hua, L-Z, 2002. List of Chinese Insects. Zhongshan (Sun Yat-Sen) University Press, Guangzhou. List of Chinese Insects 2: 1 - 612" title="List of Chinese Insects. Zhongshan (Sun Yat-Sen) University Press, Guangzhou." volume="2" year="2002">Hua (2002)</bibRefCitation>
listed as host plant also 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Casuarinaceae" genus="Casuarina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Casuarina equisetifolia" order="Casuarinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="equisetifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Casuarina equisetifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
